Avec ses mots d’enfant qui sonnent comme un monument de vérité, Tali nous met face- -face avec tous ces actes inqualifiables qui se sont produits dans son pays depuis des

Né Bonn en 1770, Ludwig van Beethoven quitte sa ville natale et s'installe définitivement Vienne en 1793 où il résidera jusqu’ sa mort en 1827. Reconnu pour son style innovateur, Beethoven a exercé une influence majeure dans le développement de la musique classique occidentale. Die Himmel rühmen des Ewigen Ehre  (“Les cieux célèbrent ta gloire”) est le premier vers du poème  Die Ehre Gottes in der Natur  du fabuliste
titre: Die Himmel rühmen des Ewigen Ehre

description: Soul Mates  (“Frères d’ me”) témoigne des liens d’amitié et de solidarité qui unissent des hommes et des femmes dans la réalisation d’un projet commun. Cette ballade harmonieuse chemine comme un long fleuve tranquille dans les méandres de la fraternité.

Seven Knights  (“Sept chevaliers”) raconte le chemin de vie de sept preux chevaliers qui ont inspiré de nombreux contes, légendes, chansons, romans et récits historiques : Robin des Bois, Tristan, Ivanhoé, Quentin Durward, Emeric, Arthur et Godefroy de Bouillon. La musique est passionnante et chevaleresque l’image des héros médiévaux qu’elle dépeint.

Electric Light Orchestra (ELO) est un groupe de rock originaire de Birmingham qui a connu ses heures de gloire dans les années 1970, décennie ouverte de nombreuses expérimentations. Celles d'ELO ont séduit par leur inventivité, s’appuyant sur une rencontre subtile entre rock, musique classique et pop. Emmené par son leader Jeff Lynne, le groupe a connu de nombreux succès tels que l’incontournable  Mr. Blue Sky .

Enjoy Life  est une œuvre simple, pétillante et colorée du compositeur allemand Wolfgang Wössner. Elle s’adresse toutes les générations de musiciens enthousiastes.Le contenu est conforme au titre : positif et joyeux. Les premier et dernier passages de l’œuvre développent une ligne mélodique fluide et vive, tandis que la partie centrale, calme et expressive, s’articule autour d’un solo pour saxophone alto.

Durant toute sa vie, Yves Montand (1921-1991) a promené son regard de velours et son immense talent sur les scènes mondiales. Il fut le chantre du music-hall l'ancienne, digne héritier de Maurice Chevalier, Édith Piaf et Charles Trénet. Dans son bagage artistique, une prestigieuse carrière cinématographique et des dizaines de chansons. Né dans le village toscan de Monsummano Alto en Italie, Ivo Livi est parti de rien

Max Steiner lance sa carrière hollywoodienne en composant la bande originale de  King Kong . Par la suite, il réalisera la musique de dizaines de films parmi lesquels  Casablanca , ou encore  Autant en emporte le vent . En 1959, il compose  A Summer Place , le thème du film éponyme de Delmer Daves, et en confie l’interprétation au Percy Faith Orchestra. Cette version sera récompensée du premier Grammy Award (1961)

Diamonds Are Forever  is both the name of the song and the name of the 1971 James Bond movie it was composed for. The original recording featured vocalist Shirley Bassey and in keeping with the original Otto Schwarz’s arrangement contains an optional part for solo voice. Depending on your needs, the vocal part can also be played by an alto or tenor saxophone or a trombone, making it an extremely verstile addition to
instrumentation: Concert Band/Harmonie and Trombone, Voice, Alto- and Tenor Saxophone

description: Considéré aujourd’hui comme un grand classique de la culture américaine, l’opéra  Porgy and Bess  (1935) fut longtemps controversé et ne connut le succès qu’après la mort de Gershwin (1898-1937). Cet excellent arrangement de Stefan Schwalgin rassemble quatre chansons emblématiques de l’opéra :  Summertime, I Got Plenty o' Nuttin’, It Ain’t Necessarily So  et  Bess, You Is My Woman Now .

Romanian Dances (Danses roumaines)  est une œuvre de commande pour l’Orchestre d’Harmonie de la ville de Balzers au Liechtenstein.La Roumanie s’appuie sur une extraordinaire richesse des traditions musicales et culturelles. Si la musique du Nord est familière l’oreille des Occidentaux, elle devient de plus en plus vive et exhubérante dans les régions du Sud. La réalisation de cette œuvre a donné lieu un

La Roumanie s’appuie sur une extraordinaire richesse des traditions musicales et culturelles. La réalisation de cette œuvre a donné lieu un intense travail de recherche. l’issue de cette phase préparatoire, Thomas Doss a effectué un choix parmi plus de mille chants collectés aux quatre coins du pays. Les six mouvements de cette œuvre (Edition complète : 1496-07-010 M) sont l’image du peuple roumain,

Des fanfares brillantes jouées par les trompettes, un passage expressif confié aux bois et un final grandiose assuré par les cuivres graves ; voici les ingrédients essentiels de cette composition.  Adventures for Band  de Gilbert Tinner est un véritable feu d’artifice !

Lamenti (Lamentations)  est un chant lent et profondément mélancolique originaire des Marches, une région d'Italie centrale. La mélodie originale est accompagnée d’un texte écrit en dialecte :« Mon bien-aimé m’a dit qu’il allait mourir.Pour lui faire plaisir, je veux mourir aussi.Trouvez quelqu’un qui chantera et jouera pour moi ;Trouvez quelqu’un qui m’enterrera… »Le thème original est exposé dans les mesures
Bass Time  met les ténors et les basses sous les feux de la rampe. Cette marche élégante et techniquement peu exigeante peut également être interprétée avec un corps de tambours ( ad lib. ).

Dans le hall du roi de la montagne  est un des plus célèbres extraits de  Peer Gynt - Suite pour Orchestre n° 1  du compositeur norvégien Edvard Grieg (1873-1907). Peer Gynt, le héros, est conduit devant le trône du roi des trolls parce qu’il a séduit une des filles du roi. La musique est sombre ; la ligne mélodique développe un chromatisme quasi diabolique. Dans cette version, signée Stefan Schwalgin, le roi de la
sous_titre: Finale from Peer Gynt Suite No. 1
titre: In the Hall of the Rocking King

description: Erinnerung an Zirkus Renz (“Souvenirs du cirque Renz”)  de Gustav Peter est un célèbre morceau de bravoure pour tous les xylophonistes. Et tous ceux qui ont déj go té aux réactions enthousiastes des musiciens et du public l’interprétation de cette œuvre, seront ravis de savoir qu’il existe désormais une autre pièce, dans la même veine, prévoir pour un prochain concert.  Running on Wood  de Stefan Schwalgin

Cette pièce de Wim Laseroms consacre le pupitre des clarinettes. Suivant la forme d’une étude classique pour clarinette, le titre de l’œuvre s’imposait comme une évidence. Élégance et virtuosité sont les maître-mots de cette composition.  Claritude  est une charmante pièce de concert qui souligne la richesse de tout Orchestre d’Harmonie.

Avec  Slidestream , Gilbert Tinner a composé une nouvelle pièce contrastante aux accents de la musique latino-américaine. Cette pièce est dédiée au pupitre des trombones. Gilbert Tinner, lui-même tromboniste, a volontairement créé une pièce sans difficultés techniques pour laisser la douceur des couleurs sonores pleinement se révéler dans l’exposition du thème lyrique.  Slidestream  dévoile les fragrances

In a Persian Market  was composed in 1920 by English composer Albert W. Ketèlby. It is a short tone poem that describes the hustle and bustle taking place at a busy, exotic Persian bazaar. Camel herders, beggars, a princess, jugglers, snake charmers and a myriad of others fill the musical scenes. The princess and her caravan eventually pass by and all is back to normal. Tohru Takahashi’s arrangement perfectly conveys

Naohiro Iwai a rassemblé trois incontournables de la musique pop desannées 1960 :  Surfin’ USA  des Beach Boys,  Hey Paula  du duo pop Paul & Paula et la musique instrumentale  Diamond Head  de Danny Hamilton, premier grand succès de la J-pop (musique pop japonaise). Avec  Sounds of the 60’s , replongez dans les sons colorés et acidulés des années 1960.

Vivenda  est une marche délicieusement charmante qui évolue en alternance entre un joyeux 6/8 et un 3/4 caractérisé par un thème cantabile. Dérivé du terme latin vivat signifiant « il/elle vit », le titre trouve toute sa signification dans l’exubérant passage forte du trio.  Vivenda  est une composition pétillante qui s’accorde avec tout programme de concert ou toute occasion festive.

Sword of Honour  (“L’épée de l’honneur”) de Tom de Haes retrace l’histoire de Gauvain, un des nobles chevaliers du roi Arthur. Gauvain apparaît essentiellement dans les premiers récits de la légende arthurienne. Il est célèbre pour avoir accepté le défi lancé par le mystérieux Chevalier vert : lui trancher la tête et le retrouver dans un an jour pour jour afin d'être son tour décapité. Fidèle sa parole, le preux et

Henry Mancini (1924-1994) fait partie des figures incontournables des compositeurs de musiques de film. Ses quarante ans de carrière furent couronnés de succès. Récompensé par quatre Oscars, les mélodies d’HenryMancini sont intemporelles. Entrez dans la magie d’Hollywood !

Broadway Impressions  est une œuvre aux parfums de la musique américaine. L’introduction est pétillante et spectaculaire. La musique nous immerge magnifiquement dans les ambiances de Broadway. Chaque pupitre dévoile ses cartes. Trois solos instrumentaux (trompette, clarinette, percussion) forment autant d’intermezzi qui interrompent la continuité de l’œuvre.  Broadway Impressions  se conclut sur un finale

Cette composition en trois tableaux évolue sur des harmonies et des rythmes pop.Unis par un thème accrocheur, le rock et la samba partent la rencontre d’un passage central lyrique. L’écriture est simple, mais efficace.  Clash of the Styles  (“Le choc des styles”) est également adapté une formation effectif réduit qui souhaite dévoiler sa richesse stylistique.

Chacun a déj plus ou moins entendu parler de  La Guerre des mondes (The War of the Worlds) . Lorsque Jeff Wayne livre sa version musicale du roman d’Herbert Georges Wells, il n’imaginait pas le succès venir. Dans l’atmosphère éthérée du tapis acoustique de  The Eve of the War , une voix sombre et intense vient appuyer la célèbre phrase « Personne n'aurait cru, dans les dernières années du XIXe siècle, que les choses
sous_titre: from The War of the Worlds

description: Schieß den Ball ins Tor  est le tube de la Coupe du Monde de Football 2006 qui s’est déroulée en Allemagne.

Marmalade for Clarinets  is a breezy solo piece from the pen of Wim Laseroms featuring the clarinet section and concert band. With this fresh and spirited composition the soloists can show off their skills and - together with the band - splendidly entertain the audience!

Toutes les régions du monde ont leurs propres traditions et coutumes, et donc leurs fêtes et célébrations nationales et locales. Celles-ci s’expriment souvent travers la musique et la danse.  Sunshine Samba  a été composé dans l’esprit d’un festival latino-américain. Dès les premières mesures, la pièce est imprégnée d’une ambiance enjouée. Cette musique au caractère spontané invite l’auditoire partager ce véritable

Song of Hope  (“Chant d’espoir”) développe une ligne mélodique principale sur laquelle de nombreux petits motifs viennent se greffer. Cette composition sereine et délicate porte en elle l’espoir d’une paix pour notre futur tous. Tel est le vœu formulé par le compositeur belge Johan Nijs. La mélodie chaleureuse et profonde rappelle qu’il est bon de prendre le temps de vivre pour ne pas se laisser emporter dans le

Solaris  de Thomas Doss illustre les instants qui précèdent une éclipse de Soleil. Dans les mesures d’ouverture, le Soleil se miroite dans l’eau lumineuse de la mer. On perçoit le chant des baleines dans le bruit du vent et des vagues. Chez la plupart des peuples anciens, le Soleil était considéré comme une divinité. Lorsqu’il s’assombrissait, ils le prirent pour un signe de la colère des dieux. Les offrandes et les

Au courant de l’été 2005, Otto M. Schwarz observe dans le ciel nocturne de l’île grecque de Kos, deux étoiles filantes qui glissent sur la vo te du firmament, se rencontrent puis se consument. Séduit par ce phénomène céleste, il choisit de livrer ses impressions dans une œuvre atmosphérique qu’il intitule  Starflash .La fanfare d’ouverture témoigne de l’immensité de l’espace, quand soudain, deux étoiles filantes

En 1966, Des Dyer et Clive Scott fondent le groupe Jigsaw. Neuf ans plus tard, ils connaissent leur premier grand succès avec la chanson  Sky High  qui se classera dans le top 3 des hit-parades internationaux et fera l’objet de nombreuses reprises, remix et autres versions. Tomohiro Tabete vous propose sa pétillante version pour Orchestre d’Harmonie.

Caucasian Sketches  (“Esquisses du Caucase”) s’inscrit pleinement dans une relation de complémentarité avec la suite  Cossack Folk Dances  (“Danses traditionnelles cosaques”). Idéalement, ces deux œuvres devraient être interprétées comme une seule et même grande fresque musicale. Les traditions cosaques se caractérisent par des danses passionnantes et des chants aux mélodies émouvantes et mélancoliques. Tout en

Petersburger Schlittenfahrt: an inspired sleigh ride through St. Petersburg in the wintertime. This work by the German Richard Eilenberg (1848-1925) is so popular in Russia that nowadaysit is thought of as a Russian composition. Franz Watz has taken this wintery, Christmas song, and made a magnificent arrangement for concert band.

Chaque année, le monde entier célèbre la naissance de Jésus au cours de la traditionnelle messe de minuit ou offices religieux divers. Les nombreux concerts autour de la Nativité font résonner des noëls anciens ou récents.  Alle Jahre wieder  est un célèbre chant de Noël allemand écrit au XIXe siècle par Philipp Friedrich Silcher (1789-1860). Ce chant annonce la venue sur terre de Jésus-Christ et l’instauration d’un

Codon du compositeur belge Kevin Houben (*1977) est un hymne la vie. Si la génétique moléculaire, véritable livre de la vie, appelle « codon » la combinaison de trois nucléotides spécifiant un acide aminé, dans cette composition, le « codon » symbolise l’interaction entre les trois pôles d’une formation : le directeur, les musiciens et le comité. Cette pièce vous entraîne dans les méandres d’une aventure palpitante et haletante au coeur de la jungle. Le premier contact révèle la dangerosité de l’enfer vert : insectes nuisibles, singes sauvages. Le danger guette derrière chaque arbre, mais la jungle est aussi apaisante et luxuriante : des oiseaux exotiques vous accueillent dans un paysage somptueux sur le chant d’une fl te en bambou. Les rayons du soleil qui

Originaire d’Écosse, saint Patrick s’installe en Irlande en 432 et parvient convertir le pays au christianisme en peu de temps. D’abord prêtre puis évêque, saint Patrick meurt le 17 mars 461. Jour férié déclaré fête nationale irlandaise, la Saint-Patrick est un jour de réjouissance célébré en l’honneur du saint évêque. De nombreuses processions et parades sont organisées cette occasion. The pop group, The Turtles, were one of the best-known bands during the 1960s with nine top 30 hits. This was quite an accomplishment considering that this era was dominated by megastars such as The Beatles, The Rolling Stones, Motown and other huge names. In 1966 The Turtles released the love song Happy Together which gave them their first number one hit single. Today this song, with its catchy chorus, is regarded

Le groupe anglo-saxon Christie a connu la gloire du jour au lendemain dans les années 1970 avec le titre éponyme de l’album Yellow River. Enregistrée pendant la guerre du Vietnam, cette chanson protestataire s’est classée au sommet des hit-parades dans plus de trente-cinq pays. Stefan Schwalgin a succombé la mélodie et au rythme entraînants de ce grand succès dont il a réalisé une version pour Orchestre d’Harmonie.

Le 1er janvier 2003, les compagnies ferroviaires suisses BVZ Zermatt-Bahn SA et Furka-Oberalp SA ont fusionné pour donner naissance au Matterhorn- Gotthard Bahn (MGB) qui parcourt un réseau de 144 kilomètres, au coeur des Alpes suisses. De Zermatt Disentis et d’Andermatt Göschenen, le MGBahn franchit un dénivelé de près de 3300 mètres, passe par 33 tunnels et galeries, franchit 126 ponts et dessert 47 gares.

Si l’instar de Franco Cesarini, vous êtes né dans un pays dont tous les horizons sont dominés par la splendeur des Alpes, vous comprendrez ce sentiment d’omniprésence de la montagne, nourriture du corps et de l’esprit dans tous les instants de la vie. Mountain Majestic est le dernier mouvement de Poema Alpestre, un poème symphonique dédié la grandeur majestueuse de la montagne ; une oeuvre somptueuse et grandiose

Cette suite est une oeuvre de commande pour l’Orchestre d’Harmonie de la ville de Vivaro située au coeur de la région autonome du Frioul-Vénétie Julienne, au nord-est de l’Italie. Pour composer cette suite, Franco Cesarini s’est appuyé sur l’immense richesse du patrimoine musical traditionnel de cette région. En 1926, le compositeur allemand Ernst Uebel compose la marche Jubelklänge qui le rendra célèbre dans le monde entier. Cette marche a été interprétée différentes occasions telles que les cérémonies du couronnement d’Élisabeth II d’Angleterre et les Jeux Olympiques d’Hiver Sapporo au Japon. Jubelklänge est une marche qui séduit tant par ses belles mélodies que par son rythme enlevé et sa légèreté dansante. Wolfgang

Tôt ou tard, chacun trouvera son me soeur, celui ou celle avec qui passer le reste de sa vie. Lorenzo Bocci a rencontré Francesca. Cette marche brillante et légère qui lui est dédiée est le tendre reflet de sa personnalité : pétillante et toujours joyeuse.

De la musique festive, des rythmes soutenus, des fanfares d’appel et un passage intermédiaire mélodieux et émouvant, telles sont les caractéristiques essentielles de Discover the Band! (“ la découverte de l’Orchestre”). Cette oeuvre de Gilbert Tinner permet de dévoiler les différentes facettes de l’Orchestre d’Harmonie. Emmenez votre public la découverte de la diversité du monde des sons !

Gilbert Tinner s’est inspiré d’une impressionnante parade de Marching Bands pour composer cette marche moderne. Les rythmes swing en 6/8 sont efficaces et simples interpréter ; les thèmes sont entraînants et ornés d’éléments caractéristiques du blues. Leur association contribue un développement énergique et toujours en mouvement. Combinant de façon idéale le swing la structure de la marche,  Step Out and Swing!

Romantic Ballad  est une œuvre courte et éthérée qui évoque un moment sublime et inoubliable de notre vie. Thomas Doss nous invite prendre le temps de nous arrêter pour revivre mentalement cette expérience passée. Chacun a connu des moments de bonheur absolu dont il se souvient avec nostalgie. Ces souvenirs découlent parfois en perles de larmes salées d’une tendresse et d’une douceur particulières.

Cette composition pétillante et légère conjugue le swing avec les syntaxes originales du Big Band, fl ne dans le monde des musiques latines, s’enthousiasme pour des rythmes rock et funk, et rebondit sur un air de two-step qui conduit l’œuvre vers un finale grandiose. Un réel succès !

Thomas Doss a dédié cette composition ses deux enfants aînés Edi et Ana-Maria. Pour bien des parents, les années de l’enfance passent trop vite. Pourtant, les journées semblent parfois interminables lorsque vos chérubins sollicitent toute votre attention et vous poussent dans vos derniers retranchements, au point de ne plus savoir où donner de la tête. Les parents ne trouvent jamais le repos nécessaire. Des genoux

Magic Overture  de Thomas Doss dépeint une promenade nocturne dans un splendide décor enneigé. Le froid glacial est vivifiant tandis que la lueur orangée des lampadaires teint la nuit d’une chaleureuse douceur. Le regard est attiré par l’atmosphère feutrée des maisons illuminées où le feu qui crépite dans la cheminée laisse deviner un havre de paix et d’harmonie. C’est dans la joie et dans la vivacité que l’on

L’Orient fascine avec ses innombrables contes, danses, parfums et saveurs. L’Orient est mystérieux et d’une sublime beauté, mais il a aussi une face cachée. Dans cette région du monde, de nombreux pays sont rongés par la pauvreté et la guerre, et sont muselés par l’oppression. Des peuples innocents vivent une terrible souffrance que seuls l’art et le chant peuvent soulager. Assis au sommet de la colline, seul avec le

Nombreux sont ceux qui considèrent les Beatles comme le meilleur groupe pop de tous les temps. Un grand nombre de leurs chansons sont devenues de grands succès et comptent parmi les chefs-d’œuvre de la musique pop.  All You Need Is Love  est un titre intemporel. Cet arrangement de Thijs Oud contient un finale remarquable dans lequel sont rassemblés plusieurs extraits de différents morceaux d’anthologie de ce

A Hard Day's Night • All You Need is Love • Let It Be • Ob-la-di, Ob-la-da • When I am Sixty Four • With A Little Help From My Friends • Michelle La musique des Beatles reste toujours aussi neuve et riche, et symbolise plus que jamais l'insouciance et la créativité des "sixties". In addition to many classic animated films the Disney Corporation has also produced many great programmes especially for television. Many of these are broadcast in the USA on a special children’s series called ‘The Disney Afternoon’. Old and young alike will recognise the melody from this classic Disney theme tune, and will be enchanted by its mesmerising Latin groove.
sous_titre: From Walt Disney's The Disney Afternoon

description: Clari-Fun-Key de Gilbert Tinner est une oeuvre pour clarinette solo et Orchestre d’Harmonie. Cette pièce se compose de deux mouvements passionnants : le style du premier mouvement s’apparente du funk rock alors que le deuxième expose un thème lyrique de bossa dans lequel la clarinette dévoile la richesse et la douceur de sa palette sonore. Clari-Fun-Key est une pièce enrichissante dans le répertoire de oeuvres pour

The Ketchup Song was a big 2002 summer hit for the Munoz sisters. The band is made up of three sisters, Lol, Lucia and Pilar who are the daughters of a famous Spanish flamenco musician called Tomate (hence Ketchup!). This fabulous arrangement will bring a taste of summer on the Costa to any concert.

Classics on Parade (“Les classiques font la parade”) de Michael Friedman est une superbe compilation de dix-neuf célèbres thèmes classiques extraits du répertoire de grands compositeurs tels que Beethoven, Mozart, Haydn, von Suppé, Offenbach, Strauss père et fils, Rossini et bien d’autres encore. Présentées avec habileté, de façon individuelle ou au contraire imbriquées les unes dans les autres, les dix-neuf pièces

Le dernier lundi du mois de juin a lieu en Suisse, la fête annuelle des enfants appelée “Solennität” (du latin solemnitas, “fête”).  Solemnitas  développe plusieurs variations et une fugue sur mélodie traditionnelle suisse que l’on chantait, jadis, durant la fête.

Little Suite for Peace (Petite suite pour la Paix)  a été composée l’occasion des festivités du 50ème anniversaire de l’École Militaire de la Logistique de Tournai en Belgique.La mission essentielle du soldat de notre temps ne consiste plus conquérir de nouveaux territoires, mais faire respecter les droits de l’homme, la liberté et plus souvent encore rétablir et maintenir la paix aux quatre coins du monde. travers

This spirited work by Andre Waignein is based on a selection of French folksongs. It consists of three movements each characterised by a particular mood. From the energetic waltz of the first movement to the simple sombre structure of the middle movement this piece takes you through many styles and emotions and will become a true favourite with your band.

Festive développe une ligne mélodique, pétillante et vive, soutenue par un thème puissant joué par les cuivres graves. Cette pièce pleine de vivacité, accessible un grand nombre d’Orchestres d’Harmonie, apporte une touche de fraîcheur tout programme de concert. Festive convient également une prestation en plein air.

Depuis la nuit des temps, la brillance et la diversité du ciel nocturne ont suscité une profonde attente et de la fascination de l’ me humaine. Combien de pensées et de rêves d’êtres de tous les temps sont rassemblés l -haut ? Un seul regard, et nous nous perdons dans l’infini de l’espace. Cette pièce a pour thème le mythe de l’Atlantide, île légendaire aux dimensions d’un continent qui, selon la mythologie grecque, fut engloutie dans l’océan par un tremblement de terre. L’œuvre retrace en trois parties l’apparition, la vie et la disparition sous les eaux de l’île légendaire qui connut la prospérité et les plaisirs de la richesse : des terres fertiles, des palais, des temples. Aurora est le nom latin de la déesse de l’aube dans la mythologie grecque, incarnant le commencement d’un jour nouveau. Dans beaucoup de cultures anciennes, l’aube a un sens spirituel : la lumière du jour est victorieuse de l’obscurité de la nuit. Dans  Aurora , Thomas Doss donne une illustration des différentes façons de saluer les premières lueurs du jour selon les cultures et les civilisations. On entend notamment

Dans le langage courant, le pathos est du pathétique facile, mélodramatique, une exagération déplacée de l’émotion. Le pathos opère la fusion entre la passion, l’émotion, le solennel et l’emphase. Il se rencontre quotidiennement dans la tonalité emphatique des articles de presse, des commentaires télévisés, des discours. Le pathétique véritable émeut profondément et douloureusement. Il dévoile et exprime la

Il Briccone  (“Le brigand”) du compositeur autrichien Thomas Doss est une marche de concert élégante qui associe virtuosité et légèreté, rythmes dynamiques et passages espiègles. La brillance des cuivres, des phrases intimistes dans un style proche de la musique de chambre et des changements de style surprenants, contribuent créer un ensemble agréablement varié. Le thème mélodique, d’une grande douceur au début de

Après avoir achevé la création de la Terre, Dieu créa l’homme et la femme. Il les bénit et leur dit : « Soyez féconds, multipliez-vous, remplissez la terre et soumettez-la. (…) ». Cette fantaisie illustre la manière dont l’homme a réellement fait usage de cette recommandation. Le passage d’ouverture décrit la création de l’être humain. Et puis très vite, l’homme part en guerre contre ses frères. L’impossibilité

sous_titre: Denkmal für die Kinder des Krieges

description: Avec Constellation, Bertrand Moren, jeune compositeur suisse, signe une marche lumineuse et éclatante pour Orchestre d’Harmonie. Divisée en deux mouvements - l’un rythmiquement dynamique, l’autre expressif et lyrique - cette marche de concert, très accessible, respire la fraîcheur et la spontanéité.

Aroldo  (1857), vingt deuxième des trente deux opéras de Giuseppe Verdi, est sans nul doute l'une des œuvres les plus méconnues du « génie de Busseto ». L'immense succès des opéras de la trilogie dite « populaire » -  Rigoletto, Le Trouvère  et  La Traviata  - composés durant cette même période détourna l'attention du public et  Aroldo  ne fut pas reconnu sa juste valeur. Cet arrangement pour Orchestre

For Franco Cesarini, who was born in a country where the majestic Alps dominates all horizons, mountains are a natural part of life. This majesty is reflected by the words of Alan Hovhaness: “Mountains are symbolic meeting places of the material and spiritual world.” In seven successive parts, Cesarini has alternated moments of reality and matter with moments of intangible spiritualism.

Ottorino Respighi est le plus connu des compositeurs italiens du XXe siècle. Il doit sa notoriété son triptyque les  Fontaines de Rome , les  Pins de Rome  et les  Fêtes Romaines . Fasciné par la musique ancienne, il s’inspire d’un recueil d’œuvres pour luth des XVIe et XVIIe siècles pour composer les trois suites de  Danses et Airs antiques . Chaque suite est constituée de quatre parties. Franco Cesarini a
titre: Antiche Danze Ed Arie Per Liuto

description: André Waignein received order of this composition of the "Municipal Brass Band of Luxembourg-Bonnevoie". It is in the presence of the Grand-Duke Heir Henri that took place first interpretation on January 24, 1998 with this orchestra, and with the composer as director.This work is a musical evocation describing this magnificent Luxembourgian region and her inhabitants.The overture evokes the serenity met in this

Showdown for Band  (Confrontation pour Orchestre) a été spécialement composé pour figurer en tant qu’œuvre imposée lors de la troisième édition du Concours International de Musique Légère de Saint-Gall (Suisse) en 1998. L’intention du compositeur était de créer une pièce de musique légère qui soit stimulante sur le plan technique pour les différents orchestres en compétition, en particulier sur le plan rythmique. La

The classic song  Stand By Me  was originally performed by Ben E King in 1960. Over the years there have been many versions of this and now there is one for wind band! This is sure to become a regular item on your concert programmes.
titre: Ben E. King: Stand by Me

description: Éditions Klostermann
In this atmospheric arrangement by Larry Foster the great melody from this hit by The Alan Parsons Project is immediately recognised. Add a bit of late seventies pop romance to your concert shedule.

titre: Wann wird's mal wieder richtig Sommer?
St. Peter und Paul / St. Johann

description: On a warm spring evening, Andrew Watkins takes you on a musical flight over the beautiful French capital Paris, the City of Lights. In this descriptive and imaginative piece, the famous sights of one of the world's greatest cities is artistically described by one of Europe's most respected composers.

L’année 1997 marquait le 150ème anniversaire des Chemins de Fer Fédéraux suisses (CFF) et la naissance de l’Orchestre d’Harmonie des CFF. L’idée de créer une telle formation émanait de Rolf Deller, un musicien passionné par les Orchestres Vent et employé des Chemins de Fer Fédéraux. Il mène bien ce projet et trouve le chef idéal : Gilbert Tinner, un musicien talentueux, diplômé de la prestigieuse Swiss Jazz School de

Frida Boccara, chanteuse française née au Maroc, eut encore plus de succès avec la ballade émouvante de 1969  Cent Mille Chansons  qu’avec sa chanson victorieuse au Grand Prix d’Eurovision, Un jour, un enfant. Larry Foster créa une version pour orchestre d’harmonie de cette chanson connue dans le monde entier, qui se prête magnifiquement l’encadrement de n’importe quelles festivités.

titre: Was wär' ein Festzelt ohne Blasmusik?

description: En 1848, Johann Strauss père (1804-1849) compose la plus célèbre de ses dix-huit marches, la  Marche de Radetzky . Cette œuvre pétillante commémore la victoire du Feld-Maréchal autrichien, le Comte Radetzky sur des insurgés Italiens, lors de la bataille de Custozza. Cette marche, souvent interprétée lors des Concerts du Nouvel An ou l’occasion de grands concerts de gala, est connue dans le monde entier.
Cum Laude  signifie « avec distinction » en latin. Une marche radieuse, qui illuminera toutes vos prestations.

On 30th September 1791, a few months before his death, the opera “Die Zauberflote” (The Magic Flute) by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart was given its first performance. It was remarkable that despite his ill health and his disastrous financial situation he was able to compose a work of such comic genius. Mozart composed the overture in the two days before the premier of the opera and it is on this overture that this

Le chant traditionnel fait partie intégrante du quotidien du peuple ukrainien. L’Ukraine s’étend sur plus de six cent mille kilomètres carrés et compte environ cinquante millions d’habitants. La nature offre de superbes paysages variés et colorés. Au nord s’étendent de vastes forêts ; l’ouest se déploient les montagnes et les vallées pittoresques des Carpates ; au centre et au sud, on trouve les steppes au sol noir

Le chant traditionnel fait partie intégrante du quotidien du peuple ukrainien. L’Ukraine s’étend sur plus de six cent mille kilomètres carrés et compte environ cinquante millions d’habitants. La nature offre de superbes paysages variés et colorés. Au nord s’étendent de vastes forêts ; l’ouest se déploient les montagnes et les vallées pittoresques des Carpates ; au centre et au sud, on trouve les steppes au sol noir

Cette composition est structurée selon la forme traditionnelle de l’ouverture (A-B-A).  Dynamic Overture  ("Ouverture dynamique") débute avec l’exposition d’un thème énergique qui sert de fil conducteur aux trois passages de l’œuvre. Dans le passage central, écrit dans un mouvement lent, le thème principal apparaît travers des phrases musicales généreuses et lyriques qui, soutenues par des harmonies amples,

Franco Cesarini a composé cette superbe fanfare de circonstance pour accompagner le grand feu d’artifice tiré dans le cadre des festivités célébrant les 700 ans de la Confédération suisse (1291-1991) Cham.  Celebration Fanfare  est une œuvre pétillante qui ajoutera une touche de brillance tout programme de concert.

Dans A Happy Band Dixie, Rob Ares s’est inspiré de la musique du Sud des États-Unis pour composer une pièce rythmée dans un style musical très apprécié pour son énergie, sa vitalité et son authenticité : le dixieland jazz.

Avec Convergents, Franco Cesarini a composé une pièce de concert très attrayante qui contient peu de difficultés techniques. Cette composition fascine surtout par son rythme audacieux. Elle comprend trois thèmes qui, après leur exposition successive, convergent au cours du finale. Convergents est une pièce enrichissante.

In 1984 the Corciano (Italy) Tourist Authority initiated a composition competition for wind band. For this event André WAignein composed "Alternances for Symphonic Band", a piece which won him the first prize in the competition. The opening of the work is based on a very tonal foundation. The English horn (or alto saxophone) introduces a rich and warm theme which is immediately taken up by the whole orchestra in a

As a trumpet player André Waignein has composed many pieces for this instrument; extremely electrifying pieces meant for young trumpet-players, and more demanding works for professionals.With his rhapsody André Waignein wanted to compose a piece in which spontaneity dominates and in which the virtuosity, sonority and style of the soloist is featured to its maximum. Although the piece is not one of the most difficult,

Your band will love getting acquainted with Mexican Pictures, a suite in four movements based on Mexican folk music. The first movement, El Butaquito, is based on a very lively folk-song of the same name and is characterised by its many contrasting rhythms. The second movement, Romance Mejicano, creates a peaceful and romantic atmosphere. The title of the third movement, Ballaviejo, means ‘Antique Dance’, in which

In the style of cinematic warhorses, the Southern Winds Fanfare is a fiery new opener for the concert band by newcomer to Wingert-Jones, composer John Dupuis. Angular melodic figures and embellishments in the woodwinds add to the excitement of this great new concert fanfare.

Carol Brittin Chambers is extremely clever in this Tarantella, as she weaves a web of wonder. Technical prowess is on full display as well as a range of styles, making this work not only exciting, but a great way to show off the sections of your ensemble.

Clearer Skies is a rhapsodic piece for the advanced high school band, depicting flight: the burst of takeoff, the smooth ride above the clouds, and a peaceful landing. Its forward momentum and more understated ending will rouse audiences for the concert finale.

Clown Car is a fresh look back at a sub-genre of marches referred to as "Circus Marches." The Composer evokes the same wonder with this work that we all had watching way too many clowns pile ot of a tiny tiny car!

The legends of old tell of brave knights, sworn to protect and defend, who vanquished dragons and saved people from tyranny. This new work for developing band, inspired by a 15th century piece titled "Agincourt Carol", is a wonderful fantasy written by Tyler Arcari. From exciting tutti sections, accessible solo moments, courtly brass fanfares and lush woodwind choirs - Defender's Oath has something for everyone.

This work opens with a punch and doesn't quit! Jorge L. Vargas brings us an intense new work perfect for opening or closing any concert program. Fun, exciting, and perfectly scored for this level Counterpunch! is going to be a favorite this season!

James Meredith slithers around this new work with twirling chromatic lines that are sure to keep players on their toes! Imagine the hiss of a cobra in a trance as it dances around the room in this clever and accessible work for the young band. Audiences will love this one, and a few might just start to dance too!
Based on a lullaby from the Yiddish Opereta Shulamith by composer Abraham Goldfaden - Raisons and Almonds has been carefully arranged by Gene Milford for the developing band.
sous_titre: Based on the Yiddish Lullaby in the Operetta Shulamith

description: This Jazzy Holiday Chart is a sure-fire way to pump up your crowd and musicians, and get everyone in the Christmas Spirit! Snap your way to success with this great new arrangement from Gene Milford!

This new, accessible march from up and coming Composer Christina Huss is the perfect introduction to march style. In a traditional style, this piece has everything you need to teach march style and put on a great show at the same time. A worthwhile chart for any concert band library.

The Hound and the Hare is a clever new work for developing band by Matthew R. Putnam that brings about an image of a more playful encounter between these two cuddly animals. More whimsical than serious, this new work is unique and a perfect centerpiece for your next concert.

Unlike its title, Inertia does anything but sit passively. From start to finish, this work delivers a wonderful melody backed by an infectious pulse. Proving yet again that an object in motion stays in motion!

Inspired by the ancient weapons masterfully crafted and yielded by Samurai – this new work attempts to display all the grandeur deserving of these legendary tools. Jim Meredith has crafted a work in homage to these beautiful, yet dangerous pieces of history.
sous_titre: The Sword of the Shogun Warrior

description: The title says it all! This new holiday hit by Mark Lortz is sure to be the talk of your winter concerts. Full of carols, and orchestrated to make your group sound big and full.
Down on the Delta is a tribute to Mississippi and its historical contributions to American music. Bluesy and fun, this new work for developing band is a winning combination!

To Soar with Broken Wings was commissioned in memory of Alex McClurg, a young man lost too soon. A Celebration of life, and a reminder that no matter what struggles you might face, you can still soar.

Winter is a truly magical season. The white snow, the long nights, the holiday lights, the festivals...it truly feels like no other time of the year. Join Composer Randall Standridge on this new wintertime journey!
This heartfelt work is uplifting and inspiring. Students will sound great with this full scoring and audiences will enjoy the film-score like qualities of composer Steve Parsons.
A perfect piece for that upcoming patriotic concert! Travis J. Weller has given us a wonderfully accessible piece for developing bands.
Take a ride into space with this fun new work for the devloping band. Composer Travis Weller invites us to go where no band has gone before!

Looking to introduce beginners to march style? Look no further than Primetime Parade! This piece is specifically written using the first 6 notes of the Bb scale, making it the ideal starting point for those just beginning to explore this unique musical style.

This clever arrangement takes the beloved carol Up on the Housetop and turns it upside down with a spooky twist. Perfect for introducing your very early players to the minor scale and a fresh new work for those first concerts!

This short three movement suite has everything you need for a complete concert experience. This wonderfully old style has been modernized for the concert band in the lowest of grade levels, making it a superior choice for teaching.

Anyone who has seen an Epaulette has probably noticed their regal beauty. That crisp, clean, and decadent view is on full display with this young march for concert band. Matthew R. Putnam knows how to write them!

An axiom is a statement or proposition which is regarded as being established, accepted, or self-evidently true. Make your band sound mature with this bold piece that includes fanfare gestures, strong themes and contrasting lyrical music. A strong choice for festival performance.
A Song of Stone and Steel is an exciting new work for beginning band by composer Tyler Arcari. Intense and with a minor sound, this new work is guaranteed to excite and motivate your young musicians!
titre: A Song of Stone and Steel

description: The Bourgeois Editions house a collection of edited masterworks, transcriptions, and arrangements of well-known musical works. Each work, beautifully engraved, has been carefully selected by one of the preeminent conductors of our time, Colonel John R. Bourgeois. Using his experience as a conductor, John brings to each score a wealth of knowledge, invaluable to the wind band conductor.

Scott Joplin has become one of the most recognizable Composers of his time, and this new arrangement of A Real Slow Drag is a unique offering in this medium. Scored beautifully by Col. John R. Bourgeois, this one will be a great addition to any serious concert library.

The Bourgeois Editions house a collection of edited masterworks, transcriptions, and arrangements of well-known musical works. Each work, beautifully engraved, has been carefully selected by one of the preeminent conductors of our time, Colonel John R. Bourgeois. Using his experience as a conductor, John brings to each score a wealth of knowledge, invaluable to the wind band conductor.

sous_titre: from Le Voyage dans la Lune

description: This clever old march has been brought back in an accessible grade 3 by arranger Van B. Ragsdale. Uniquely including a chorale in the middle of this march, National Spirit is a must have for your march library!

The title says it all! Intense from start to finish, Intensity is a tour de force for the concert band. Keep your audience on the front of their seats and your musicians engaged and ready to play with this fiery new work by Gary Ziek!
This old march, now scored as an accessible grade 3, is brought to the fore by arranger Laurie Lafferty. Your horn in F players will appreciate the inclusion of the melodic line!
This new reduced instrumentation fanfare is a perfect opener to your next concert. Copeland-like rhythmic figures and the cinematic depth of modern film-scores make this one an instant concert hit.

Beacons was written to celebrate the career of a legendary teacher from Alabama. She has been a champion for small school bands and created one of the most renowned band programs in the state. Her motto is “Be a Light”.

To Dream With Open Eyes captures the sense of wonder, imagination, and possibility that turns dreams into reality. Soaring melodies, lush harmonies, and energetic rhythms bring a cinematic feel and exciting lyricism to this work for concert band!
A Salute to band directors everywhere, Festive Fanfare is a bold new work for the concert band by composer Terry White. You and your students will love it!
This classic march has been scored for grade 3 concert band by Arranger Van B. Ragsdale. Accessible and full of musical challenge, this new edition is a must for your concert library!
Voyager is a fast-paced tour de force for the concert ensemble. Fun to play and scored so each section has interesting parts, this piece is perfect as a concdert opener or closer.
This work, dedicated to the tireless spirit of his students, is a great new addition to the concert music library. John M. Pasternak's music is cinematic and fun for both musicians and audiences.

Gene Milford has a way with folk melodies and the like, and The Bold Grenadier is no exception. Almost brooding, this lovely work in the style of the old greats like Vaughan Williams or Holst is a sure hit!

Take a wild ride through a haunted house with this new work perfect for Halloween concerts. John Dupuis has given us an accessible work with lots of stuff to chew on…well, that is, if Ghosts had teeth!

Tyler Arcari has a knack for smashing un-related tunes together, especially for Christmas! This clever new addition to Tyler’s chaotic caroling is no exception. Musicians will love the drama in this work, as they mix Poor Wayfaring Stranger with the likes of God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen and Patapan. This will be the star of your next holiday program!
sous_titre: (Poor Wayfaring Stranger, Patapan, God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen)

description: The definition of gravitas (dignity, seriousness, or solemnity of manner) perfectly describes the style of this piece. It contains some carefully placed descending dissonance in the introductory material that is used throughout the piece to make even the youngest of students sound bold!
Flagship is a great teaching piece for bands wanting to explore 3/4 time. John knows how to score a band to sound big and full!

Trains are a part of Christmas, whether on a “trip” to the North Pole or around the Christmas tree. With train effects and a happy melody interspersed with familiar carols this will be a favorite of players and audience alike.

This is a classic novelty selection that features a group of soloists playing actual kitchen utensils. A popular light concert selection with additional suggestions (such as having your soloists dressed as cooks) included in the score. An audience favorite for many years.
Transcribed for concert band from Hartleys earlier Ballet Music. A brief prologue moves into a bright, flashy march that allows each section of the ensemble to have a moment in the sun.
This beautiful pastorale is the second movement of Gillis Symphony No.1. (7 minutes)
sous_titre: 2nd MovT From Symphony No. 1 For Band

description: An excellent arrangement of this well known orchestral finale. Suitable for concert or contest programming, it will provide an appealing change of sonority and color. (5 minutes, 45 seconds)

This beautiful work uses lyrical themes, rich scoring, gentle percussion, and dynamics to paint a picture of quiet reflection of the day that has passed, then builds to a dramatic climax before peacefully fading into the night. There are several opportunities for flute and clarinet solos. A perfect choice for concert or contest, this work provides an excellent opportunity to teach breath control, phrasing, tone, and

This excellent work provides a very high-energy yet very accessible musical experience. A brisk tempo, driving rhythms, interesting colors, solid percussion, huge impacts, rising tension, and plenty of dynamic and articulation contrasts provide nonstop excitement for both players and concertgoers. Low brass gets plenty of features, and brass ranges are very comfortable.

Based on the holiday favorites Jolly Old St. Nicholas and Up on the Housetop with a rousing nod to Joy to the World as the finale, this delightful and engaging arrangement is perfect for a young band's first holiday concert. The two main themes creatively intertwine, with each section getting a chance to play the melody. A trumpet countermelody, glissandos, and even playful woodblock and cowbell solos make this a
This exciting arrangement for mature concert band features adaptations of three dances by Brazilian composer and pianist Ernesto Nazareth: 1. Odeon 2. Floraux 3. Bregerio.

With all the regality and bravura of the original, this powerful arrangement from Act III of Wagner's Lohengrin is the perfect choice to showcase the brilliant sounds of the brass choir and the technical displays of the woodwind section. Additional scoring calls for two euphoniums, two timpani, and eight off-stage trumpets.
An authentic, lively, spirited, and accessible arrangement for concert band of Scott Joplin's celebrated ragtime waltz.

Quite possibly the oldest inhabited fortress in history, Edinburgh Castle evokes emotions of mystique and wonder. This work, scored for beginning bands, uses mysterious themes, creative orchestration, dynamics and percussion to take the listener on a musical journey through the dark corners of the old castle. Excellent for teaching blend and playing with soft dynamics. Optional bass part.

A visit to New York City inspired this vibrant concert work, supercharged with the urban buzz of one of the most amazing places in the world. The speed of life and the collision of so many personalities, ideas, and cultures is energizing and invigorating. Adapted from the original for reduced instrumentation ensembles, this is a concert celebration that pulsates with the urban groove one feels when walking through

The West Coast is famous for being at the forefront of technology and innovation; it is also an area of great natural beauty. This duality inspired the staccato musical elements that create a digital effect against the contrasting lyrical melodies that represent vistas of breathtaking landscapes. A wonderfully colorful musical mosaic of this vibrant part of our country. Adapted for ensembles with reduced

A powerfully creative work, expertly adapted from the original composition for smaller bands that evokes all the danger and excitement of a grand and ferocious battle - at sea, on land, or even on some far-off planet. The end result is a creative concert work that uses both symphonic and cinematic language that will appeal to a broad range of players and audiences.

Welcome the holidays in a grand and festive manner! Adapted from the original to be playable by bands with limited instrumentation, the familiar holiday melodies of Joy to the World; Bring a Torch, Jeanette, Isabella; The First Noel; I Saw Three Ships and hints of others are skillfully overlapped to create an enthralling seasonal presentation. It's completely delightful and sure to get everyone's Christmas season off

This intense and volatile piece lights the fuse with a one-bar introduction that leads to and ignites the impact of the full band. A unifying four-note motif makes several expanded appearances. A brief period of calm is underpinned by a series of pulsating ostinati which maintain a constant state of agitation. In the explosive conclusion, the percussion section provides the last word with one final detonation.

A spirited holiday opener or closer where the composer's love for percussion is proudly evident. Three traditional Christmas tunes are featured, including I Saw Three Ships; Bring a Torch, Jeannette, Isabella and We Three Kings of Orient Are. Each carol is introduced and then combined and overlapped for a rousing effect complete with a crisp percussion transition. An unexpected and lively 7/8 ending brings the work
titre: Christmas in the Valley of the Kings

description: Roughly translated as "seize the day," Carpe Diem is a celebratory message of inspiration. It is easy to get caught up in the daily business of life, trapped in memories of the past while waiting anxiously for what is to come. This spirited work challenges the listener to cherish the present, take advantage of what "now" has to offer, and recognize all the gifts that today brings.

Reward your students while taking the audience on a thrilling sonic journey. Part fanfare and part overture, this work pays homage to the great works students have experienced for generations. It opens with a majestic brass fanfare complemented by colorful woodwinds and percussion. A variety of textural and stylistic presentations leads to the closing flourish that rises from the bottom of the sound canvas to the top

The beauty, anticipation and drama of the first Christmas Eve is reflected in this collage of familiar classical melodies and timeless carols. The famous Children's Prayer from the opera "Hansel and Gretel" frames settings of Away in a Manger; Infant Holy, Infant Lowly; Brahms's Lullaby (Wiegenlied) and the Welsh folk song All Through the Night. A wonderfully peaceful setting that creates a welcome moment of quiet

This lively and appealing march is one of the most widely recognized works of classical literature and one of the most popular concert marches. The catchy rhythms and stylish melody have made this a programming favorite for concert bands since it was first written. Arranged here to be playable by developing bands, this delightful work can now be appreciated and enjoyed by a new generation of musicians and their

Much like the prophecies of ancient seers, musical works have the power to communicate the profound. Shrouded in mystical sounds, the opening creates an air of mystery and intrigue as though peering through time at misty images of future events. As the visions grow and take shape, the music intensifies, leading to bold musical proclamations that will make a lasting impression.

Energetic and percussive, this dynamic fanfare is exciting for both listeners and performers. The high intensity, memorable theme, and fast tempo are the perfect elements needed to grab everyone's attention and announce that the performance has begun. Aptly titled, this fiery selection is certain to make a lasting impact on your next performance.

Here is a musical homage to all the tales of otherworldly apparitions that gave everyone goosebumps as a child. The evocative music takes the listener on an eerie journey through a series of musical vignettes, each representing a spooky story that might be told around a campfire or when the power goes out. Come listen as we summon ghosts and conjure up spirits; but listeners beware... leave the lights on!

"Oh! I have slipped the surly bonds of Earth..." Inspired by the poem "High Flight” this work takes musical flight with sweeping woodwinds and mallets soaring above the cinematic melodic statement by brass. The highly rhythmic melody soars upward to the middle, lyrical section which seems to float effortlessly through the upper reaches of the sky. As the sustained expressive melody reaches it's musical apex it

A brisk and lively selection that welcomes the holidays in a grand and festive style. The familiar holiday melodies of Joy to the World; Bring a Torch, Jeanette, Isabella; The First Noel; I Saw Three Ships and hints of others are skillfully overlapped to create a totally enthralling and energetic seasonal presentation. It's completely delightful and is sure to get everyone's Christmas season off to a bright and

The powerful writing of this majestic work will allow young students to express their energy and enthusiasm through strong full band passages. The emphatic and unrelenting rhythms create an ominous atmosphere as the commanding image of this mighty warship slowly comes into view. Unyielding and incessant, it draws ever closer, bringing a full array of musical weaponry to bear.

Pursuing his interest in the Turkish peoples, the composer created this work for orchestra in 1930. It is a richly melodic suite notable for its characteristically oriental turns of phrase. This work is presented in four movements: Caravan, which depicts a steady journey over rolling sand dunes; At Rest, alternately tranquil and spirited; Night, serene in nature with a slight touch of mystery; and Festival, a

This delightful stop-time two-step dance was first published in 1902, and its appeal is as widespread today as it was then. A new sense of vibrancy and optimism is reflected in this early 20th century dance that features the wild "new" rhythms of ragtime which substantially changed the nature of dance. Lively and rhythmic, this work displays all the features that made the style so popular and shows the composer to be

Julius Fucik was born in Prague, Bohemia in 1872 and died in Berlin, Prussia in 1913. A bassoonist and composer, he later became the most renowned bandmaster on the Continent. This masterful march creates a vivid display of musical imagery as it begins in 6/8 time depicting the majestic galloping rhythm of horses associated with the cavalry. The march then continues in alla breve meter featuring bold and profound

This award-winning musical work was inspired by a poem written by an American Civil War soldier in 1864 after being captured and sent to the notorious Andersonville Prison. Expressive music captures the indomitable spirit of the soldiers words and the underlying sense of optimism in the face of unrelenting adversity. The heartfelt themes will leave listeners with a strong sense of optimism for the future despite the

This piece is joyful and celebratory, ideal for opening or closing a concert and useful for any time of the year. There are a number of triumphant fanfares throughout followed by short flourishes that create a vibrant sound canvas. Several optional solo parts can give more accomplished musicians an opportunity display their skills and which vary the overall texture of the work. Inspiring, encouraging, and uplifting!

Nikola Tesla was one of historys greatest inventors. Teslas Dream begins with a soft, contemplative flute solo, backed by gentle mallet percussion as though we are witness to his "lucid dreaming," which he believed was the source of his most creative ideas. This theme is repeated, growing to a full ensemble impact which represents the moment of creation and inspiration coming to fruition. The music then becomes

A collection of Australian folk songs that depict the sights and sounds of the beautiful landscape with an Aussie twist and tongue-in-cheek tuneful way. The first movement includes The Wonderful Crocodile and The Old Jig-Jog, folk songs full of energy and dance-like qualities. River Fraser provides the melodic content for the second movement, a slow and impassioned lament. The third movement uses three popular tunes

Pele is the Hawaiian goddess of fire, lightning, wind, and volcanoes. According to legend, she lives in Kilauea, one of the worlds most active volcanoes. The chant of her devotees while Kilauea spews lava and fire into the sky is the basis of this composition. The first of four connected sections is Tribute, where the chant starts as a solo voice that adds weight to the chant with each repetition. The Awakening

A musical tale of a lone watchman, vigilant at his outpost by the desolate sea. His quiet thoughts of home and loved ones are soon displaced by the sudden appearance a fleet of invaders. The tempo increases as the ships draw near and he sounds the alarm; soon the battle is on! Aggressive music reflects the fierce conflict as both sides push back and forth before the battle turns in favor of the village guard. As the

A bold and sweeping introduction of regal grandeur immediately greets the listener before this brisk work launches into a buoyant main theme. This lively section is bubbling with a joyful spirit fueled by sparkling rhythms and bright, uplifting melodic lines. A peacefully idyllic interlude creates a reflective mood of repose before a repeat of the vibrant opening brings the piece to an uplifting and exuberant finale.

Santa bought a newfangled toy assembly machine, and the elves have been assigned to keep this beast running! The percussion section gets to take center stage as they portray this contraption that continually breaks down despite the frustrated elves frantic efforts to keep it going. The favorite carol Jolly Old St. Nicholas (and a slight nod to Mr. Pachelbel) acts as the musical adhesive that holds this amusing

This striking march has been transcribed and carefully arranged for young bands so they can experience the thrill of performing works from the classical orchestral repertoire. The regal style of the original is displayed brilliantly in this setting which provides a rewarding and contrasting performance selection. It can also be used as a processional march for graduation or ceremonial occasions.

As the title suggests, three popular carols are combined to create a cheerful holiday setting that is sure to brighten the mood of the season. Good King Wenceslas opens the piece on a very festive note, followed by a lyric yet energetic presentation of God Rest Ye Merry, Gentlemen. The piece closes with The First Noel for a musical and full-sounding finish that will leave a warm and satisfying feeling for all.

All the positive energy implicit in the title is superbly displayed in the seemingly boundless spirit of exuberant music. A majestic opening paves the way for an energetic and substantial work for young bands. This creative selection is well suited to be the main focus of any concert, either as a concert opener or featured program selection.

Inspired by T.E. Lawrences memorable book The Seven Pillars of Wisdom, this musical adaptation is a descriptive account of the authors role in the Arab revolt during World War I. The music captures the imagery and mood of the desert landscape through three musical scenes: The Hills of Hejaz at Dawn; The Attack on Akab and Audas Furious Charge, all of which are enhanced through the use of colorful percussion.

These mighty beasts of legend and lore were believed to wield almost limitless might and power. Clad in a coat of virtually impenetrable scales, armed with claws like steel and breath of fire, these were truly fearsome and awe-inspiring creatures. The vision of an epic battle between these great monsters is depicted, replete with percussive sounds of impact as they collide with one another while winds and brass

This celebratory piece for younger bands uses driving percussion and rhythmic ostinatos to create an overall sense of energy and passion for excellence. Opening with a resplendent fanfare, the music gains momentum, constantly moving forward, even through a softer section of longer note values. After introducing a new syncopated motive the initial fanfare returns, this time supported by an intense rhythmic pulse to

Those pesky interstellar visitors from outer space are back! In earlier works in this "Aliens" series, these other-worldly characters with their grand plan of taking over our planet were defeated - but now theyve returned with a vengeance! Even the special sound effects return, adding to the eerie and mysterious atmosphere that surrounds the extraterrestrial invaders.

Programmatic in nature, this work depicts the opening of the first operational steel mill in the United States. Carefully written so it can be performed in the first year of instruction, it uses only the first notes learned in most beginning band methods. Young players will be able to have the experience of performing a mature-sounding composition with reasonable technical demands and fun special effects.

This very playable treatment of the traditional Christmas carol Here We Come A-Wassailing is the perfect selection for your beginners very first holiday concert. This arrangement changes the 6/8 and 2/4 time of the original to a far more accessible 4/4 throughout and the ranges and rhythms are well within the capabilities of first-year musicians. This festive setting will have elementary bands welcoming the holiday

Commissioned by the 2004 Harford All-County Middle School Band, Maryland. A strong sense of suspense is established at the very outset, permeating the musical fabric throughout the entire piece to create a very effective, attention-grabbing concert opener. An unsettled and relentless rhythmic pulse drives the work forward, provided at various times by woodwinds, brass, and percussion, keeping the listener on edge

Portal, Nebraska, was one of many once-vibrant towns on the early frontier, full of ambition, determination, and pioneering spirit. Like many of these small communities, its long gone but its memories live on. Contrasting themes and musical colors paint a vibrant picture of frontier life on the great plains in the late 1800s.

The Van Buren High School Bands (Arkansas) commissioned this piece in honor of their long time band director upon his retirement. The lively and melodic quality of the opening reflects his spirit and the constant energy he applied to his teaching on a daily basis. A quiet and serene middle section provides a lyric, serene contrast, as if pausing for a moment of reflection before the opening material appears again for

Hymn and Celebration is specifically written for advanced middle school or younger high school ensembles. More proficient groups will find the ranges, rhythms, and technique to be less challenging but at the same time will find an opportunity to explore and perform contrasting styles in music. This work provides an exceptional medium to teach and reinforce syncopation, articulation, phrasing, and meter changes.

A garden is a magical place. In addition to the vegetables, fruits, herbs and flowers, there are also numerous species of wildlife attracted by the plants; buzzing insects and a variety of birds add their musical songs. To spend time in a garden is to experience a wide variety of entrancing sounds, and the effect is quite musical. Experience a relaxing journey into that world as the band takes you aurally into The

George Washington and the Continental Armys withdrawal from Philadelphia to Valley Forge was one of the darkest chapters of the Revolutionary War. The demoralized mood of the troops is conveyed by the Revolutionary-era hymn Chester in a minor setting. A tempo change ushers in a new spirit as the Continental Army perseveres through the harsh winter and becomes a hardened fighting force. Finally, Chester is

When arranging a familiar holiday favorite, the challenge is always to hear it in a completely new way. As more and more versions of these well-known classics flood the market every year, it becomes harder to see each tune in a new light. This setting takes the popular Ukrainian Bell Carol and uses it to create a gentle presentation in the style of a lyric lullaby that truly reflects the peaceful and most appealing

This famous circus march has been a favorite of bands and audiences for years, and this well-crafted arrangement puts it easily within the reach of less experienced musicians. It will sound great with young players and provide a thrilling march addition to concert or contest programs. The solid and well-doubled scoring will sound impressive on any program and will provide the same feeling of excitement as the

Tides are typically associated with the daily rise and fall of the oceans. Tides of Change revolves around a simple yet evolving two-measure motive that evokes images of lifes triumphs and challenges. The gently moving melodic line ebbs and flows, creating an almost hypnotic effect that immerses the listener in the warmth and peace of this moving work for young band.

Starburst is dedicated to the Johnston County Eighth Grade All-County Middle School Band in Benson, North Carolina. Its a sparkling work that was specifically written to feature all sections of the band. Attention is immediately focused on the hard-driving full-ensemble introduction that moves into a feature for the woodwinds and horns. The trumpets then get the spotlight, followed by a brief woodwind interlude that

Nova Stella: New Star Fanfare is based on the chorus of the traditional English carol, Nova! Nova! Ave Fit Ex Eva. The fanfare begins with three or more antiphonal brass players placed throughout the concert hall. Large percussion forces, which includes optional parts, are used to help introduce the rest of the ensemble as they join in the musical celebration. As the full ensemble joins in, the combined efforts of

This vivid fanfare features rousing brass motives, dynamic woodwind flourishes and active percussion, all combining to create an explosive concert opening statement. Beginning quietly, the action builds quickly, accelerating into a spinning sonic dynamo that truly befits the title. Every section has actively rhythmic parts that keep the action moving forward. Technical demands kept at a very playable level while
titre: Moving at the Speed of Sound

description: The music of A Golden Legacy reflects both the joy and reverence many of us feel in our role as transmitters of the band tradition. The legacy in the title refers to the long-lasting impact directors have on students lives. This piece alternates between two themes - the first is a majestic fanfare that develops into a purposeful and resolute march; the second theme is a reverent hymnlike chorale that undergoes

The rousing march music of John Philip Sousa has been an audience favorite for generations and continues to hold an important place in concert band repertoire. This spirited medley combines themes from four of Sousas most famous marches: The Washington Post; Semper Fidelis; The Thunderer and The Stars and Stripes Forever for an entertaining and stylish setting that will highlight any concert program. Great for any

Wonders of the Seasons is aptly named, as it combines a variety of well-known Christmas melodies in a variety of styles. Opening with a bold setting of O Come, All Ye Faithful, almost every section of the band is featured with fragments of a number of different Christmas melodies layered on top of one another throughout. Other carols presented are God Rest Ye Merry, Gentlemen and Silent Night, with Angels We Have

Shady Grove is a folk song that began to be heard in the southern Appalachians around the time of the Civil War. The memorable melody has a distinctively haunting quality that one cant help but be affected by. Many different lyrics exist for the song (some estimate it could be as many as 250), but the central themes are that of longing, love, and friendship. The use of washboard and spoons at one point brings this

Scarborough Fair is simply one of the most beautiful and haunting melodies of all time, and this setting incorporates the favorite melody to captures the sounds and mood of a gray and rainy afternoon. The melancholy melody matches up perfectly with the the sounds of gently falling rain and the faint, distance rumbles of thunder. Rain and thunder sound effects, though not essential, can be added with recordings.

The music of Revolution is bold and restless and, like most revolutions, combines passionate, hopeful and anxious undercurrents. Mounting levels of musical tension build relentlessly like a restless mob that grows as it charges through the streets, leading to the initial statement of the melody. A quiet waltz-like section slows the action, gradually taking on a more anxious and almost sinister nature which then

The Pinnacles National Park is known for its breathtaking spires and rock formations; these breathtaking vistas are all represented in this musical presentation. The delicate sounds of the tranquil opening reflects a quiet dawn, gradually building as more instruments are added. The glorious scenery unfolds as the sun rises and reveals the panoramic beauty. A remarkable musical representation of this true wonder of

Before Their Time commemorates the tragic passing of two students in a car accident. The lives of youth are precious; when we lose them abruptly it magnifies the loss. The expressive opening captures the bittersweet emotions before moving into a more active section that reflects all the energy and vigor of youth. The natural energy of the music builds to a glorious moment and two musical climaxes punctuate the

Bright, lively and extremely appealing, this spellbinding Latin-flavored concert work displays all the harmonic color and syncopated rhythms one expects to find in this popular style. The wide range of percussion instruments add to the exotic flavor and overall hypnotic effect that the alluring melodies create. The intriguing title has a double meaning in that the music is in the style of a sultry rhumba and rhumba

Of Wind and Fire is a spirited and energetic concert opener or closer for young bands. The music drives relentlessly from start to finish with energetic eighth notes passages traded between various segments of the band. The addition of spectacular texture and dynamic changes add to the overall appeal and young bands will sound remarkably mature when playing the bold melodic statements that occur in the opening and

Edgar Allan Poe is perhaps most well known for his writings on Gothic topics, darkness, and early forms of science fiction, and he almost single-handedly created the genre we now call the detective story. This work effectively captures the darkness that so poignantly defines Poe, the writer. The slow, brooding introduction captures the dark moods that characterize so much of his writing. The second section envisions

This work musically conjures up faint images of ominous, shadowy figures and dark, mysterious rituals from ancient times in faraway lands. The mystical sounds of the wind instruments are brewed together with ample portions of colorful and varied percussion sounds to create a magical musical potion that will cast an appealing and irresistible spell that listeners cant help but enjoy.

Heres a light and entertaining work for first-year musicians thats the perfect vehicle for teaching and reinforcing playing in 3/4 time. As the title implies, its meant to be a fun and good-humored piece that makes learning and playing fun. It begins with the full ensemble and then allows the woodwinds and then brass to perform separately, making the piece easy to rehearse and prepare while teaching rhythmic

Just about everyone who has been to summer music camp has come home with a bucketload of fun stories about the many activities. Campfire Song has its origin in such a story and even includes the sound effects of a crackling campfire. The melody started as an inside joke in the form of a catchy, impromptu song that had its first and last performance at a camps season-end campfire. This setting is meant to be a fun

Arabian Dreams captures the mystique and sense of adventure that surrounds the picturesque desert land of Arabia. The exotic sounds begin slowly and mysteriously, leading to a lively tempo change and dance-like feel that is introduced by the percussion section. The colorful harmonies provide a great opportunity to introduce young musicians to the use of accidentals, making this an educational as well as an

Joseph F. Lamb is rightfully regarded as one of the "Big Three" composers of classic ragtime music, the other two being Scott Joplin and James Scott. Lamb, who was of Irish descent, was the only non-African American of the group. Unlike Joplin and Scott, Joseph Lambs fame outlived the era of classic ragtime and he, along with Eubie Blake, were the only personalities from the original ragtime era that took part in the

Ignacio Cervantes (1847 - 1905) was a Cuban pianist and composer who achieved fame and recognition in his native country. Cervantes is best known for his considerable influence in blending various aspects of creole musical culture with that of Cuban music for a totally unique and appealing sound tableau. Four of Cervantes colorful dances are included in this brilliant setting for wind band. They are Danzas Nos. 1 and

Also titled Aria With Diverse Variations, this monumental opus for harpsichord was composed and published late in Bach's career. The composition represents a unique blend of complexity, beauty, and massive scope. In this setting, the aria and all 30 variations are presented in different combinations of instruments making it the perfect vehicle for featuring various chamber ensembles within the larger performing

In commenting about this march, Sousa is reported to have said "(its) addressed to no particular nation, but to all of Americas friends abroad." His words couldnt have been more prophetic as it has become the musical symbol of international friendship and goodwill. As director of the Marine Band, Col. John R. Bourgeois has performed this march on numerous historic occasions such as the 100th anniversary of the

Relentless is an aggressive and hard-charging piece for concert band that was inspired by the belief that we all, in our own way, have the ability to be unstoppable if we choose to be. Inside everyone there is a pool of positive energy, determination, and drive that, when utilized, can overcome any obstacle or hardship. We must all call on this inner strength and resolve to be relentless in the pursuit of our dreams

Power Play was commissioned by band director Robert Ball and the Mill Creek Middle School Band, Shawnee, Kansas. This exciting addition to young band repertoire was written to deliver an energetic element to concert programs. Pushing the tempo will help players develop their technique and, along with exaggerating the accents, will contribute to the driving force of the piece. While the overall effect sounds

Keystone Regatta was commissioned by the bands of Cleveland, Glenpool, and Skiatook, Oklahoma in recognition of Steve and Mary Snider and their outstanding commitment and contribution to the music students of eastern Oklahoma. The regal opening and spirited themes treat the listener to an impressive musical presentation that also serves as a fitting tribute to these two dedicated and respected music supporters.

Centrifuge was written for the 2015 Southeastern Louisiana Middle School Band Camp and its director, Paul Frechou. This piece portrays the a centrifuge vigorously spinning with no sign of slowing down or stopping. An allegro tempo is used to fuel the drive and impetus throughout this energetic musical depiction of a whirling perpetual motion dynamo. The opening theme is first presented by clarinets playing in their

This creative work is one more addition to a series of band pieces that musically describe the fictional saga of an alien invasion. In this installment, the mysterious and persistent visitors from outer space are continuing their quest for world domination with a new and formidable weapon, a giant robotic android. Massive and ominous, it clanks along seemingly unstoppable as the alien troops march forward, bent on

The Thunderer was written by "The March King," John Philip Sousa, in 1889; it was said that it was Mrs. Sousas favorite march. This well-known march is adapted here for young bands and still retains all the charm and appeal of the original. With the woodwind parts lowered and the rhythms and snare drum part simplified, its very playable by most middle school bands. Its a great way for young musicians to experience

The folk song Ten Thousand Miles, also known as The Turtle Dove, captures the essence of the Aeolion mode in a warm, somber, yet flowing melodic line. Appearing in numerous versions, the song is a musical gem that has been passed down in various forms from one folk singer to another. The song may have originated as a 17th century broadside; though many well-known composers have used it as inspiration, this version

Rondeau Royale was carefully composed to address the needs of both advancing and developing band students. The melody, countermelody and accompaniment include varied articulations as well as changes in dynamics and texture. Its written in a rondo form where, after the introduction, the main theme is stated, followed by short episodes that change the texture and character of the piece. The title Rondeau Royale takes

The Christmas season is an exciting time filled with wonder and marvel and is certainly the most musical time of the year - everywhere we turn we are treated to the festive "sounds of the season."
